{
  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Sanjay versus State of Uttar Pradesh pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_2_1790_1805','2025INSC317'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SANJAY<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF UTTAR PRADESH </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1790</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 317</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003532025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The Appellant/accused was convicted under Section 302 IPC and 376(2)(G) IPC for alleged murder of a four-year-old girl. The Trial Court convicted the Appellant and sentenced him to death, which was later confirmed by the High Court. The High Court confirmed the sentence dead body was recovered following the accused&rsquo;s disclosure and was identified by PW1, the victim&rsquo;s father. The last-seen evidence was firmly established through the testimonies of PW1, PW2, PW3, PW6, and PW7, confirming that the victim was last seen with the accused. The<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 239/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_2_1790_1805','2025INSC317','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='